-- Candover Seeks $642 Million Qioptiq Defense Company Sale, Telegraph Says
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2010-10-31T15:15:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-31/candover-seeks-642-million-qioptiq-defense-company-sale-telegraph-says.html
Candover Investments Plc , a U.K.
private-equity firm, is preparing to sell defense company
Qioptiq for 400 million pounds ($642 million), the Sunday
Telegraph said, without saying where it got the information.  N.M. Rothschild & Sons Ltd. is preparing the possible sale
for the second quarter of 2011, the newspaper said.  Candover spokesman  Peter Hewer  declined to comment when
contacted by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Chris Kay  in London at 
